00:00:08.920 --> 00:00:11.950
Chrome 45 is rolling out now.

00:00:11.950 --> 00:00:16.600
There's new ATMOS script 2015
functionality, improvements

00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:19.560
to app install banners,
and a new security

00:00:19.560 --> 00:00:23.750
feature to ensure that no one
is messing with your code.

00:00:23.750 --> 00:00:26.090
From the Empire Hotel
in New York City,

00:00:26.090 --> 00:00:29.250
let's take a look at
what's new in Chrome.

00:00:29.250 --> 00:00:33.240
Over the past year, we've added
a number of new JavaScript

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:37.970
features, defined in the ATMOS
script 2015 specification,

00:00:37.970 --> 00:00:41.060
formerly known as ES6.

00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:45.990
In Chrome 45, we've added
support for arrow functions.

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:48.750
Beyond the shorter
syntax, they eliminate

00:00:48.750 --> 00:00:51.940
the need for dot
bind or the var self

00:00:51.940 --> 00:00:56.540
equals this hack necessary
for anonymous functions,

00:00:56.540 --> 00:01:00.410
because they lexically
bind the this value.

00:01:00.410 --> 00:01:03.450
Arrow functions may take
some getting used to,

00:01:03.450 --> 00:01:05.200
but once you've
played with them,

00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:08.040
they become second nature.

00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:10.560
Jason Orendorff
has a detailed post

00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:14.660
on arrow functions
on hacks.Mozilla.org.

00:01:14.660 --> 00:01:17.920
You can find the link in
the description below.

00:01:17.920 --> 00:01:20.670
There are new methods
on the array object,

00:01:20.670 --> 00:01:24.660
like from, of,
fill, find, and find

00:01:24.660 --> 00:01:29.560
index, that make dealing
with arrays much easier.

00:01:29.560 --> 00:01:33.150
On Android, you can now defer
the add to the home screen

00:01:33.150 --> 00:01:36.690
banner and show it at a
more convenient time, when

00:01:36.690 --> 00:01:40.230
it doesn't interrupt
the application flow.

00:01:40.230 --> 00:01:42.700
Simply prevent
the default action

00:01:42.700 --> 00:01:47.480
by calling preventDefault on
the before install prompt event

00:01:47.480 --> 00:01:50.620
and save a reference
to the event for later.

00:01:50.620 --> 00:01:53.200
Then, when you're
ready, re-trigger

00:01:53.200 --> 00:01:57.250
the prompt by calling
prompt on the stored event.

00:01:57.250 --> 00:02:00.920
We've also added the ability
to install native apps,

00:02:00.920 --> 00:02:02.940
directly from your site.

00:02:02.940 --> 00:02:06.300
It works in much the same
way as add to home screen.

00:02:06.300 --> 00:02:09.660
Your site needs to
be served over HTTPS,

00:02:09.660 --> 00:02:13.180
have a web app manifest file
that includes information

00:02:13.180 --> 00:02:14.770
about your native app.

00:02:14.770 --> 00:02:19.510
Then, if a user visits your site
at least twice over a two week

00:02:19.510 --> 00:02:22.130
period, they'll see the banner.

00:02:22.130 --> 00:02:23.930
Check the link in
the description

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:26.060
below for full details.

