00:02:32.770 --> 00:02:36.920
To help protect users,
sub-resource integrity

00:02:36.920 --> 00:02:39.430
provides a mechanism
for the browser

00:02:39.430 --> 00:02:42.060
to verify that a
fetch resource has

00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:46.240
been delivered without
unexpected manipulation.

00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:50.490
You can use this to mitigate
the risk of a compromised server

00:02:50.490 --> 00:02:54.680
or ensure that only carefully
reviewed third party code

00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:56.520
is executed.

00:02:56.520 --> 00:03:00.990
This helps to ensure that the
expected resource is used,

00:03:00.990 --> 00:03:06.080
not just any resource that
lives at a particular URL.

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:09.190
The current spec
and implementation

00:03:09.190 --> 00:03:15.010
covers only script and link
rel equals stylesheet elements.

00:03:15.010 --> 00:03:17.340
Once the file has
been retrieved,

00:03:17.340 --> 00:03:21.120
the browser compares
the hash of the file

00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:23.760
to the hash provided
by the integrity

00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:25.570
attribute of the element.

00:03:25.570 --> 00:03:29.200
If the hashes don't match,
the browser won't use it.

